# Atomic Design (UI)

UI in this repo lives under `app/ui/` (e.g. `app/ui/atoms/`, `app/ui/molecules/`). Adjust paths below if you add `organisms/` or `templates/`.

## Structure
Organize UI as Atomic Design: atoms/molecules/organisms/templates/pages
- Place components in smallest appropriate level
- Don't skip levels without reason
- Favor composition over inheritance

## HTML Elements Rule (STRICT)

**Native HTML elements can ONLY be defined in atoms. Period.**

### Forbidden elements in molecules/organisms/templates
The following elements **MUST NOT** appear directly in molecules, organisms, or templates:
- Container elements: `div`, `span`, `section`, `article`, `aside`, `header`, `footer`, `nav`, `main`
- Form elements: `form`, `input`, `textarea`, `select`, `label`, `fieldset`
- Text elements: `p`, `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `h4`, `h5`, `h6`, `span`, `strong`, `em`
- List elements: `ul`, `ol`, `li`, `dl`, `dt`, `dd`
- Table elements: `table`, `tr`, `td`, `th`, `thead`, `tbody`
- Media elements: `img`, `video`, `audio`, `canvas`
- Interactive elements: `button`, `a`, `details`, `summary`

### What to do instead
If you need any of these elements in a molecule/organism/template, you **MUST**:
1. Create an atom that wraps the HTML element
2. Use that atom in your component

### Visual-only conditional rendering
For `condition && <UI />` and similar **purely visual** gating in molecules/organisms/templates, use the guard atoms pattern described in `.cursor/skills/atomic-design-ui/SKILL.md` (`RenderOrNull`, `RenderOrFallback`).

### Examples

**❌ WRONG - HTML elements in molecule:**
```tsx
// app/ui/molecules/SearchBar/SearchBar.tsx
export const SearchBar = () => {
  return (
    <div>  // ❌ NEVER use div in molecules
      <input type="text" />  // ❌ NEVER use input in molecules
      <button type="button">Search</button>  // ❌ NEVER use button in molecules
    </div>
  );
};
```

**✅ CORRECT - Using atoms:**
```tsx
// app/ui/atoms/Box/Box.tsx
export const Box = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => {
  return <div>{children}</div>;  // ✅ HTML element in atom
};

// app/ui/atoms/Input/Input.tsx
export const Input = (props: React.InputHTMLAttributes<HTMLInputElement>) => {
  return <input {...props} />;  // ✅ HTML element in atom
};

// app/ui/atoms/Button/Button.tsx
export const Button = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => {
  return <button type="button">{children}</button>;  // ✅ HTML element in atom
};

// app/ui/molecules/SearchBar/SearchBar.tsx
import { Box } from "@app/ui/atoms/Box/Box";
import { Input } from "@app/ui/atoms/Input/Input";
import { Button } from "@app/ui/atoms/Button/Button";

export const SearchBar = () => {
  return (
    <Box>
      <Input type="text" />
      <Button>Search</Button>
    </Box>
  );
};
```

## Testing
- New UI components should have tests covering behavior
- Use Vitest + React Testing Library
- Test via user-visible output and interactions, not implementation details

## Verification Commands
```bash
# Check for HTML elements in molecules (should return nothing)
grep -rE "<div|<span|<input|<button|<p|<h[1-6]" app/ui/molecules/ --include="*.tsx"

# When you add organisms, point grep at app/ui/organisms/ similarly

# Check atoms (should find HTML elements)
grep -rE "<div|<span|<input|<button|<p|<h[1-6]" app/ui/atoms/ --include="*.tsx"
```
